.vice.com/test-uploads/_uncategorized/1588176637235-Screenshot_20200429-104345.png" alt="AI Meme Generator 7"><div class="article__image-caption"></div></div><p>&quot;Nothing about the text generation is hardcoded, except that the maximum text length is limited for sanity,&quot; according to the site description. &quot;The model uses character-level prediction, so you can specify prefix text of one or more characters to influence the text generated. Using someone&apos;s name or other short text as a prefix works best.&quot; </p> <p>In making the generator, Wenzlau didn&apos;t filter profanity from the public data used for training, he warned on the site. A troublesome aspect of machine learning is that, without proper interventions, systems can pick up on biases and prejudices in the training data. I did encounter one slightly racist meme, but most of them are very pure and good. </p> <p>And often, painfully topical for the times we&apos;re in.</p><div class="article__media"><img src="https://video-images.vice.com/test-uploads/_uncategorized/1588176618432-image-5.png" alt="AI Meme Generator 6"><div class="article__image-caption"></div></div>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1588176660;}}s:7:"channel";a:5:{s:5:"title";s:22:"VICE US - undefined US";s:11:"description";s:22:"RSS feed for undefined";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Thu, 30 Apr 2020 17:56:33 +0000";s:7:"tagline";s:22:"RSS feed for undefined";}s:9:"textinput";a:0:{}s:5:"image";a:0:{}s:9:"feed_type";s:3:"RSS";s:12:"feed_version";s:3:"2.0";s:8:"encoding";s:5:"UTF-8";s:16:"_source_encoding";s:0:"";s:5:"ERROR";s:0:"";s:7:"WARNING";s:0:"";s:19:"_CONTENT_CONSTRUCTS";a:6:{i:0;s:7:"content";i:1;s:7:"summary";i:2;s:4:"info";i:3;s:5:"title";i:4;s:7:"tagline";i:5;s:9:"copyright";}s:16:"_KNOWN_ENCODINGS";a:3:{i:0;s:5:"UTF-8";i:1;s:8:"US-ASCII";i:2;s:10:"ISO-8859-1";}s:5:"stack";a:0:{}s:9:"inchannel";b:0;s:6:"initem";b:0;s:9:"incontent";s:9:"enclosure";s:11:"intextinput";b:0;s:7:"inimage";b:0;s:17:"current_namespace